Introduction to Artificial Intelligence
Artificial Intelligence (AI) refers to the simulation of human intelligence in machines that are programmed to think and learn. These systems are capable of performing tasks such as problem-solving, pattern recognition, language understanding, and decision-making.
AI systems are broadly categorized into narrow AI and general AI. Narrow AI focuses on specific tasks such as image recognition or speech processing, while general AI aims to perform any intellectual task that a human can do.
The growth of AI has been driven by increased computational power, availability of large datasets, and advancements in machine learning algorithms.

