Machine Learning Fundamentals
Machine Learning (ML) is a subset of Artificial Intelligence that focuses on enabling machines to learn from data without being explicitly programmed. ML algorithms identify patterns in data and improve performance through experience.
There are three main types of machine learning:
Supervised Learning
Unsupervised Learning
Reinforcement Learning
Supervised learning involves labeled datasets, whereas unsupervised learning works with unlabeled data. Reinforcement learning focuses on learning optimal actions through rewards and penalties.

