Deep Learning and Neural Networks
Deep Learning is a specialized branch of machine learning that uses artificial neural networks with multiple hidden layers. These networks are inspired by the structure of the human brain.
Neural networks consist of input layers, hidden layers, and output layers. Each neuron applies a weighted sum followed by an activation function to produce outputs.
Deep learning models have achieved state-of-the-art performance in areas such as computer vision, natural language processing, and speech recognition.

